research_insight_text_link.research_insight_description: Artemis Health is focused on advancing health data analytics through genetic analysis techniques. Their research includes methods for determining copy number variations in nucleic acid mixtures, which is crucial for identifying genetic differences. Additionally, they have developed apparatus and methods for enriching components or cells from samples, enabling SNP genotyping and diagnostic results for fetal disorders. Their work also encompasses methods and kits for selectively enriching non-random polynucleotide sequences, facilitating the detection of fetal aneuploidy. These innovations contribute to the field of prenatal diagnostics and genetic research.

overview_description.description:
Artemis Health operates as a health data analytics company. It operates a platform that provides self-insured employers with actionable data on their benefits programs, opportunities and gaps, and tools to help them make decisions. 

Artemis Health's platform enables users to identify problems in their benefits’ programs; share findings with the right people; find solutions for problems and to enhance their programs; and track solutions. Dallen Allred, Dallin Regehr, and Grant Gordon founded it in 2013, with its headquarters in Salt Lake City in Utah.
